Class OpenstackCreateVirtualMachineStrategy

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.uniulm.omi.cloudiator.sword.drivers.jclouds.strategy.JCloudsCreateVirtualMachineStrategy
      • de.uniulm.omi.cloudiator.sword.drivers.openstack.strategy.OpenstackCreateVirtualMachineStrategy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.google.common.base.Function<VirtualMachineTemplate,VirtualMachine>, CreateVirtualMachineStrategy

    public class OpenstackCreateVirtualMachineStrategy
extends JCloudsCreateVirtualMachineStrategy
    Create virtual machine strategy for Openstack.

    Uses the extension points of JCloudsCreateVirtualMachineStrategy to support availability zones and hosts.

    For this purpose it modifies the virtual machine template by setting the region of the availability zone/host so that jclouds validation does not fail.

    Afterwards it modifies the template options object and manually sets the availability zone there.
